</m:math>, about the same as without the capacitor. The capacitor has a smaller effect at high frequencies.
</para></solution>
    </exercise><exercise id="fs-id1169737930730" type="problems-exercises">
        <problem id="fs-id1169737118482">
          <para id="import-auto-id1169738086377">An <emphasis effect="italics">RC</emphasis> circuit consists of a
<m:math>
 
  <m:mi>40.0 Ω</m:mi>
 
</m:math> resistor and a
<m:math>
 
  <m:mtext>5.00 μF</m:mtext>
 
</m:math> capacitor. (a) Find its impedance at 60.0 Hz and 10.0 kHz. (b) Compare these values of <m:math>
 
