          <exercise id="fs-id1169738137511" type="problems-exercises">
            <problem id="fs-id1169737924005">
              <para id="import-auto-id1169737763460">An <emphasis effect="italics">RLC</emphasis> series circuit has a <m:math>
 
  <m:mi>1.00 kΩ</m:mi>
 
</m:math> resistor, a <m:math>
 
  <m:mi>150 μH</m:mi>
 
</m:math> inductor, and a 25.0 nF capacitor. (a) Find the circuit’s impedance at 500 Hz. (b) Find the circuit’s impedance at 7.50 kHz. (c) If the voltage source has <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>rms</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mtext>408</m:mtext></m:mrow><m:mspace width="0.25em"/><m:mtext>V</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:math>, what is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>I</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>rms</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> at each frequency? (d) What is the resonant frequency of the circuit? (e) What is <m:math><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>I</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>rms</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow></m:math> at resonance?</para></problem>
<solution id="fs-id1169737844573">
    <para id="import-auto-id1169737827160">(a) <m:math>
 
  <m:mi>12.8 kΩ</m:mi>
 
</m:math></para><para id="import-auto-id1169737827162">(b) <m:math>
 
  <m:mi>1.31 kΩ</m:mi>
 
</m:math></para><para id="import-auto-id1169737827164">(c) 31.9 mA at 500 Hz, 312 mA at 7.50 kHz</para><para id="import-auto-id1169737827167">(d) 82.2 kHz</para><para id="import-auto-id1169737788984">(e) 0.408 A</para>
    </solution>
    </exercise>

